text:
Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

The current president of the United States is shell shocked. He sees that the world is completely different. China has created war androids that have taken over much of the world. They are a technological nightmare. The world looks like a dystopian horror story. Taiwan, Japan, Africa, and Europe are now under the control of the Chinese Communist Party.

The United States has to stop the Chinese military, but they are no match for Chinaâ€™s war machines. They hire the best scientists they can find to quickly develop an anti-android destroyer. They are deployed in the dark of night to help reclaim territories.

Unfortunately, there isn't much success, so the president decides to drop atom bombs on all of the android factories in China. The explosions are so large, they ignite the atmosphere. The civilian casualties are enormous, but not as enormous as they would have been had the Chinese Communist Party been allowed to continue its world domination.

The American president felt bad about the civilian casualties but felt that they were necessary to bring justice back to the world. He tells the Chinese to disband and allow free elections. They disagree, and everyone knows that they will use nuclear weapons to protect their power. As a response, the USA bombs the entirety of China and completely obliterates it. 

The world breathes a huge sigh of relief and mourns civilian casualties while also celebrating the return of freedom. The world is finally at peace, but it will be a long time before America gets over the horror of what they had to do.
